as prepared by mixing CsBr (0.4 mmol), PbBr2 (0.4 mmol), oleylamine (OLA, 0.5 mL), and oleic acid (OA, 1 mL) in DMF (10 mL) (Figure S1a). Both DMF and toluene were dried from any remaining traces of water prior to use (DMF by adding KnNa12 n[(AlO2)12(SiO2)12], and toluene via distillation). When investigating the influence of water added to the \"bad solvent\", 1 mL of the dry precursor was injected into a mixture of toluene and water (10 mL + x μL, 0≤x≤60) (Figure S1c). When investigating the influence of water added to the precursor, 1 mL solution taken from the mixture of 1 mL dry precursor and x μL (0≤x≤60) water was injected into dry toluene (Figure S1d).\n\nOutput:\n(\"entity\"<|>CsPbBr3 NCs<|>Product<|>Cesium lead bromide nanocrystals, the target product of the synthesis)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>LARP<|>Synthesis method<|>Ligand-Assisted Reprecipitation approach used for synthesis)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>Precursor mixture<|>Precursor<|>Mixture of reagents used to form CsPbBr3 NCs)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>Toluene<|>Solvent<|>Organic solvent used in the synthesis process)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>CsBr<|>Reagent<|>Cesium bromide, a source of cesium for the nanocrystals)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>PbBr2<|>Reagent<|>Lead bromide, a source of lead for the nanocrystals)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>Oleylamine<|>Reagent<|>Organic compound used in the synthesis, abbreviated as OLA)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>Oleic acid<|>Reagent<|>Organic acid used in the synthesis, abbreviated as OA)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>DMF<|>Solvent<|>Dimethylformamide, solvent used to prepare the precursor)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>KnNa12 n[(AlO2)12(SiO2)12]<|>Drying agent<|>Compound used to remove water traces from DMF)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>Room temperature<|>Reaction condition<|>Temperature at which the synthesis was carried out)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>1 mL<|>Dosage<|>Volume of precursor mixture injected)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>10 mL<|>Dosage<|>Volume of toluene used)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>0.4 mmol<|>Dosage<|>Amount of CsBr and PbBr2 used)\n##\n(\"entity\"<|>0.5