\"relationship\"<|>Oleic acid<|>CsPbBr3 NCs<|>OA acts as a surface ligand for CsPbBr3 NCs<|>3)\n##\n(\"relationship\"<|>Oleylamine<|>CsPbBr3 NCs<|>OAm acts as a surface ligand for CsPbBr3 NCs<|>3)\n##\n(\"relationship\"<|>Toluene<|>CsPbBr3 NCs<|>Toluene acts as an antisolvent to induce the formation of CsPbBr3 NCs<|>4)\n##\n(\"relationship\"<|>Zr(OC4H9)4<|>ZrO2<|>Zr(OC4H9)4 is the precursor for ZrO2 coating<|>5)\n##\n(\"relationship\"<|>ZrO2<|>CsPbBr3@ZrO2 NCs<|>ZrO2 forms a coating on CsPbBr3 NCs to create CsPbBr3@ZrO2 NCs<|>5)\n##\n(\"relationship\"<|>Room temperature<|>CsPbBr3@ZrO2 NCs<|>The synthesis of CsPbBr3@ZrO2 NCs is carried out at room temperature<|>3)\n##\n(\"relationship\"<|>1500 rpm<|>CsPbBr3 NCs<|>Vigorous stirring at 1500 rpm is used during the synthesis of CsPbBr3 NCs<|>3)\n##\n(\"relationship\"<|>8500 rpm<|>CsPbBr3@ZrO2 NCs<|>Centrifugation at 8500 rpm is used to purify CsPbBr3@ZrO2 NCs<|>3)\n<|COMPLETE|>\n\n\n-Real Data-\n######################\ntext: }_{0.6})_{3}@\\mathrm{PS}$   was relative  low (results not shown here). The slow diffusion of nano crystals  and sluggish movement of polymer chains at low temperature  which result in a lower efficacy of impregnation.  \n\nThe average PL lifetime of   $\\mathrm{Cs}\\mathrm{Pb}{\\mathrm{Br}}_{3}@\\mathrm{PS}$   composite is \n\n 56.8 ns, while that of the pristine   $\\mathrm{Cs}\\mathrm{Pb}{\\mathrm{Br}}_{3}$   nano crystal is   $7.9\\;\\mathrm{ns}$   \n\n (Figure 2b), which implies that the nano crystals were packed into  PS matrices, and, simultaneously, the change of environment of  \n\n![](https://imgbed.siat-mic.com/i/2024/09/23/2c030a92c0bbc72dd0e7d8af7673a1f03972058f0dcd533ed59dc59c2a222341-1727077292.jpg)  \nFigure 2.  ${\\mathsf{P Q D s}}{\\@\\mathsf{P S}}$   composites: a) emission peak and FWHM of   $\\mathsf{C s P b}(\\mathsf{C l}_{0.5}\\mathsf{B r}_{0.5})_{3}$  ,   $\\mathsf{C s P b}(\\mathsf{C l}_{0.4}\\mathsf{B r}_{0.6})_{3}$  ,   $\\mathsf{C s P b}(\\mathsf{C l}_{0.3}\\mathsf{B r}_{